Screen.Name: Screen 1
Zone.Name: continueButton
Arguments: To extend moral consideration to animals, acknowledging their right to bodily autonomy and freedom
anything_else:
The only "argument" I usually accept from NON-vegans is the "I don't care about animals enough to stop eating/abusing them". If they can acknowledge that it is an irrational preference, that they value their pleasure more than the lives of these animals, I can respect that position as the only one that is consistent.

Most of the non-vegans I have encountered however don't come to this "argument" from the start, they get to it much later in the discussion.

I don't hold anyone that cannot be vegan for (diagnosed) medical reasons or for food availability accountable. All others have a choice, they are just lazy about their ethics and their efforts.
